        "theoretical_or_simulated",
        "scripts"
      ],
      "raw_data_description": "Raw data are described as sequencing reads and biological samples: PacBio subreads (6.01 M subreads, 47.88 Gb) from a male H. erectus, Hi-C reads from an adult male H. erectus, and Illumina paired-end reads from 358 specimens across 21 species. The paper does not indicate that raw FASTQ/BAM files are deposited in the text excerpt, but raw sequencing data were clearly generated and used for assembly, mapping, and variant calling.",
      "processed_data_description": "Processed data include the assembled H. erectus genome (420.66 Mb, 22 superscaffolds), filtered SNP datasets, pairwise genetic distances, nucleotide diversity estimates (theta_pi and theta_w), ortholog CDS matrices, gene trees, species trees, divergence-time estimates, neutral loci for G-PhoCS, PSMC-derived Ne histories, candidate positively selected genes, and bmp3 amino-acid substitution summaries. These are described as analysis outputs rather than primary measurements.",
      "figure_data_description": "Yes. The paper explicitly says source data are provided for figures and/or in Figshare datasets. Figure captions mention 'Source data are provided as a Source Data file' for Fig. 1 and Fig. 3, and 'Source data are available at Figshare' for Fig. 2. Fig. 4 also states source data are provided as a Source Data file. Supplementary datasets are referenced throughout.",
      "scripts_description": "No standalone analysis scripts or notebooks are explicitly mentioned as deposited. However, the Methods list many software tools and command-line pipelines used for analysis (WTDBG, Pilon, BWA-MEM, FreeBayes, ANNOVAR, PLINK, MEGA, smartPCA, ANGSD, ASTRAL, BEAST/starBEAST2, G-PhoCS, PSMC, PAML/codeml, RAxML, SPREAD, Juicebox, 3D-DNA, Juicer). The text also mentions 'in-house scripts' for translating reconstructed CDS sequences into protein sequences.",
      "notes": "The dataset is a mix of primary sequencing data and heavily processed downstream outputs. The paper emphasizes figure-ready source data and Figshare-hosted analysis datasets more than raw file deposition. Several datasets are modality-specific: Dataset 1 (diversification rate / phylogeny), Dataset 2 (nucleotide diversity), Dataset 3 (ortholog alignments), Dataset 4 (gene trees and ASTRAL species tree), Dataset 5 (BEAST divergence-time analysis), Dataset 6 (spatial diversification reconstruction), Dataset 7 (PSMC demographic histories), Dataset 8 (positive selection / dN/dS tables), Dataset 9 (protein trees). External or compiled data are also used, e.g. sea-level change from a prior study. The paper does not describe a dedicated repository for raw reads in the excerpt, so raw-data availability is partially unknown from the provided text."
